cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a workflow that uses computer vision methods to automatically extract candidate cadastral boundaries from UAV orthoimages and a tool for their semi-automatic processing to delineate final cadastral boundaries. The methods used in the workflow are gPb contour detection and SLIC superpixels, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) techniques, which are relevant to the development of the tool.
